\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2157\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.scala-lang:scala3-library_3:3.0.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"number\":2156,\"title\":\"Support for org.scala-lang:scala3-library_3:3.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2156\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"number\":2155,\"title\":\"Support for org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2155\"},{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nCurrent `org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:4.2.0` still fails in a GraalVM native image, and the existing metadata published under `metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1` does not resolve it.\\n\\nThis came from validating Micronaut Kafka issue `micronaut-projects/micronaut-kafka#1213` against the current `6.0.x` line and then checking whether the existing reachability metadata helps.\\n\\nUpstream issue links:\\n- Micronaut Kafka issue: https://github.com/micronaut-projects/micronaut-kafka/issues/1213\\n- Validation comment being followed up here: https://github.com/micronaut-projects/micronaut-kafka/issues/1213#issuecomment-4305176848\\n\\n## What I verified\\n\\n### 1. Old 3.9.1 failure is **not** the current 6.0.x failure\\n\\nThe older Micronaut Kafka issue comment validated `kafka-clients:3.9.1` failing in native execution with:\\n- `ClassNotFoundException: java.security.AccessController`\\n- `NoSuchMethodException: javax.security.auth.Subject.current()`\\n\\nOn the current Micronaut Kafka `6.0.x` line, the managed Kafka client version is `4.2.0`, and the current native failure is different.\\n\\n### 2. Current `kafka-clients:4.2.0` failure\\n\\nI built a minimal Micronaut app against the current Micronaut Kafka `6.0.x` source and let it create a Kafka producer on startup with:\\n- `security.protocol=SASL_PLAINTEXT`\\n- `sasl.mechanism=PLAIN`\\n- `sasl.jaas.config=org.apache.kafka.common.security.plain.PlainLoginModule required username=\\\"admin\\\" password=\\\"admin-secret\\\";`\\n\\nThe native executable fails before any broker handshake with:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.apache.kafka.common.config.ConfigException: Invalid value org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever for configuration sasl.oauthbearer.jwt.retriever.class: Class org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever could not be found.\\n    at org.apache.kafka.common.config.ConfigDef.parseType(ConfigDef.java:789)\\n    at org.apache.kafka.common.config.SaslConfigs.addClientSaslSupport(SaslConfigs.java:388)\\n    at org.apache.kafka.clients.producer.ProducerConfig.<clinit>(ProducerConfig.java:526)\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Existing metadata does not resolve it\\n\\nI checked the current metadata tree for `org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients` and found:\\n- only `metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1`\\n- `index.json` marks `3.5.1` as latest and lists tested versions `3.5.1` and `3.5.2`\\n\\nI then vendored the current `3.5.1/reachability-metadata.json` directly into the reproducer under:\\n\\n```text\\nsrc/main/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/reachability-metadata.json\\n```\\n\\nRebuilding the native image did increase the reflected-type count, so the metadata was being consumed, but the runtime failure remained exactly the same:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.apache.kafka.common.config.ConfigException: Invalid value org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever for configuration sasl.oauthbearer.jwt.retriever.class: Class org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever could not be found.\\n```\\n\\n## Why the current metadata appears insufficient\\n\\nThe published `3.5.1` metadata contains entries such as:\\n- `javax.security.auth.Subject`\\n- `org.apache.kafka.common.security.plain.PlainLoginModule`\\n- `org.apache.kafka.common.security.authenticator.DefaultLogin`\\n- `org.apache.kafka.common.security.authenticator.SaslClientCallbackHandler`\\n\\nBut it does not appear to include the OAuth bearer defaults that now fail first for `4.2.0`, such as:\\n- `org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever`\\n- `org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtValidator`\\n\\n## Reproducer\\n\\nEnvironment used:\\n- Linux aarch64\\n- GraalVM CE 25.0.2\\n- `native-image 25.0.2`\\n\\n### App code\\n\\n`settings.gradle`\\n```groovy\\npluginManagement {\\n    repositories {\\n        gradlePluginPortal()\\n        mavenCentral()\\n    }\\n}\\n\\nrootProject.name = \\\"mkafka-1213-6x-app\\\"\\nincludeBuild(\\\"/path/to/micronaut-kafka-6.0.x-worktree\\\")\\n```\\n\\n`build.gradle`\\n```groovy\\nplugins {\\n    id \\\"io.micronaut.application\\\" version \\\"4.6.2\\\"\\n}\\n\\nrepositories {\\n    mavenCentral()\\n}\\n\\ndependencies {\\n    implementation(platform(\\\"io.micronaut.platform:micronaut-platform:4.10.11\\\"))\\n    implementation(\\\"io.micronaut.kafka:micronaut-kafka\\\")\\n    implementation(\\\"io.micronaut:micronaut-runtime\\\")\\n    annotationProcessor(\\\"io.micronaut:micronaut-inject-java\\\")\\n    runtimeOnly(\\\"org.slf4j:slf4j-simple:2.0.17\\\")\\n}\\n\\napplication {\\n    mainClass = \\\"example.Application\\\"\\n}\\n\\nmicronaut {\\n    version(\\\"4.10.11\\\")\\n    runtime(\\\"none\\\")\\n    testRuntime(\\\"junit5\\\")\\n    processing {\\n        incremental(true)\\n        annotations(\\\"example.*\\\")\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`src/main/resources/application.properties`\\n```properties\\nmicronaut.application.name=mkafka-1213-6x-app\\nkafka.bootstrap.servers[0]=127.0.0.1:19093\\nkafka.security.protocol=SASL_PLAINTEXT\\nkafka.sasl.mechanism=PLAIN\\nkafka.sasl.jaas.config=org.apache.kafka.common.security.plain.PlainLoginModule required username=\\\"admin\\\" password=\\\"admin-secret\\\";\\n```\\n\\n`src/main/java/example/Application.java`\\n```java\\npackage example;\\n\\nimport io.micronaut.runtime.Micronaut;\\n\\npublic final class Application {\\n    private Application() {\\n    }\\n\\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\\n        Micronaut.run(Application.class, args);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`src/main/java/example/TasksClient.java`\\n```java\\npackage example;\\n\\nimport io.micronaut.configuration.kafka.annotation.KafkaClient;\\nimport io.micronaut.configuration.kafka.annotation.Topic;\\n\\n@KafkaClient\\npublic interface TasksClient {\\n    @Topic(\\\"tasks\\\")\\n    void send(String body);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`src/main/java/example/StartupSender.java`\\n```java\\npackage example;\\n\\nimport io.micronaut.context.event.ApplicationEventListener;\\nimport io.micronaut.context.event.StartupEvent;\\nimport jakarta.inject.Singleton;\\n\\n@Singleton\\nfinal class StartupSender implements ApplicationEventListener<StartupEvent> {\\n    private final TasksClient tasksClient;\\n\\n    StartupSender(TasksClient tasksClient) {\\n        this.tasksClient = tasksClient;\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public void onApplicationEvent(StartupEvent event) {\\n        System.err.println(\\\"Sending Kafka message from startup listener\\\");\\n        tasksClient.send(\\\"hello\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Dummy listener\\n\\nA real Kafka broker is not required because the failure happens before the full broker handshake. A plain TCP listener is enough:\\n\\n```sh\\nperl -MIO::Socket::INET -e '$|=1; my $s=IO::Socket::INET->new(LocalAddr=>\\\"127.0.0.1\\\",LocalPort=>19093,Proto=>\\\"tcp\\\",Listen=>5,Reuse=>1) or die $!; while (my $c=$s->accept) { select(undef,undef,undef,30); close $c; }'\\n```\\n\\n### Build and run without vendored metadata\\n\\n```sh\\n/path/to/micronaut-kafka-6.0.x-worktree/gradlew -p /tmp/mkafka-1213-6x-app nativeCompile\\ntimeout 20s /tmp/mkafka-1213-6x-app/build/native/nativeCompile/mkafka-1213-6x-app\\n```\\n\\nObserved failure:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.apache.kafka.common.config.ConfigException: Invalid value org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever for configuration sasl.oauthbearer.jwt.retriever.class: Class org.apache.kafka.common.security.oauthbearer.DefaultJwtRetriever could not be found.\\n```\\n\\n### Build and run with the currently published metadata vendored in\\n\\nAdd the published metadata file from:\\n\\n```text\\nmetadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/reachability-metadata.json\\n```\\n\\nto:\\n\\n```text\\nsrc/main/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/reachability-metadata.json\\n```\\n\\nThen rebuild and rerun the same commands above.\\n\\nObserved result:\\n- native image still builds successfully\\n- runtime failure is unchanged\\n- same `DefaultJwtRetriever could not be found` exception\\n\\n## Requested follow-up\\n\\nPlease add or update `org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients` metadata so that the current client line used here (`4.2.0`) is covered and the native runtime no longer fails during SASL config initialization.\\n\\nAt minimum, this looks like it needs coverage for the OAuth bearer default classes that are now eagerly referenced during config initialization.\\n\",\"number\":2110,\"title\":\"org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:4.2.0 native image still fails without oauthbearer defaults; existing 3.5.1 metadata does not resolve it\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2110\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.activemq:activemq-client-jakarta:5.18.5\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\n_No response_\",\"number\":1962,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.activemq:activemq-client-jakarta:5.18.5\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1962\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-reflect:1.6.10\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"number\":1955,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-reflect:1.6.10\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1955\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core-jvm:1.6.4\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"number\":1956,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core-jvm:1.6.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1956\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-compiler-embeddable:2.3.20\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nAllow kotlinc native images.\",\"number\":1952,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-compiler-embeddable:2.3.20\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1952\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.grpc:grpc-util:1.80.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"number\":1751,\"title\":\"Support for io.grpc:grpc-util:1.80.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1751\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jspecify:jspecify:1.0.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"number\":1750,\"title\":\"Support for org.jspecify:jspecify:1.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1750\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.grpc:grpc-netty-shaded:1.80.0\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nGPRC internally shades netty and uses it for serving, this should ideally be similar to netty\",\"number\":1749,\"title\":\"Support for io.grpc:grpc-netty-shaded:1.80.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1749\"},{\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.ehcache:ehcache:3.3.1\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nhttps://github.com/ehcache\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Contribution preference\\n\\n- [ ] I want to provide support myself and don't want the AI generation to do it for me.\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nUnable to use EhCache with Native Image of Apache Camel & Quarkus.\\n\\n### Logs and error messages\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: java.lang.IllegalStateException: org.ehcache.core.spi.ServiceLocator$DependencyException: Failed to find provider with satisfied dependency set for interface org.ehcache.spi.resilience.ResilienceStrategyProvider [candidates []]\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.core.spi.ServiceLocator$DependencySet.build(ServiceLocator.java:351)\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.core.EhcacheManager.resolveServices(EhcacheManager.java:157)\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.core.EhcacheManager.<init>(EhcacheManager.java:128)\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.core.EhcacheManager.<init>(EhcacheManager.java:118)\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.core.EhcacheManager.<init>(EhcacheManager.java:114)\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.config.builders.CacheManagerBuilder.newCacheManager(CacheManagerBuilder.java:115)\\n\\n\\tat org.ehcache.config.builders.CacheManagerBuilder.build(CacheManagerBuilder.java:71)\\n\\n\\tat com.edb.esb.cache.CacheConfig.cacheManager(CacheConfig.java:30)\\n\\n\\tat com.edb.esb.cache.CacheConfig_ProducerMethod_cacheManager_QkJFKjxcCpLXrTsWPUF0S_ejVaQ_Bean.create(Unknown Source)\\n\\n\\tat com.edb.esb.cache.CacheConfig_ProducerMethod_cacheManager_QkJFKjxcCpLXrTsWPUF0S_ejVaQ_Bean.create(Unknown Source)\\n\\n\\tat io.quarkus.arc.impl.AbstractSharedContext.createInstanceHandle(AbstractSharedContext.java:119)\\n\\n\\tat io.quarkus.arc.impl.AbstractSharedContext$1.get(AbstractSharedContext.java:38)\\n\\n\\tat io.quarkus.arc.impl.AbstractSharedContext$1.get(AbstractSharedContext.java:35)\\n\\n\\tat io.quarkus.arc.generator.Default_jakarta_enterprise_context_ApplicationScoped_ContextInstances.ch13(Unknown Source)\\n\\n\\tat io.quarkus.arc.gener